Why Shell in DevOps?

1. Infrastruture
2. Coding
3. Configuration Management

To read the output in a better way, we can use

./filename | more

To run a shell script in debug mode, you can use the -x option with the shell interpreter. This mode prints each command and its arguments as they are executed, making it easier to debug the script.

Example

#!/bin/bash
echo "This will not be debugged"
set -x
echo "This will be debugged"
set +x
echo "Debugging turned off"

